modules.description: Handles conversion and validation of IP addresses between string and binary formats for both IPv4 and IPv6. Manages MAC address parsing, formatting, and comparison. Validates input formats and ensures correct representation in network byte order.

Converts between Cstructs and MAC address values by parsing 6-octet sequences into Macaddr.t instances and serializing Macaddr.t values into 6-byte Cstructs. Handles error conditions with result types or exceptions based on the function used. Used in network protocol implementations to encode and decode Ethernet addresses.
